        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 24 at 7:34PM EDT by NWS Detroit/Pontiac MI</headline>
        <description>At 734 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Quanicassee, or near Reese, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Caro, Cass City, Reese, Akron, Fairgrove, Unionville, Gagetown,
Quanicassee, Ellington, Gilford, Wisner, Colling, and Colwood.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
